  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Cost & Receiving Officer",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Summary</strong></h3><p>The Cost & Receiving Officer is responsible for receiving, inspecting, and recording all goods delivered to the hotel, while ensuring accurate cost control and compliance with hotel policies. This role plays a key part in safeguarding hotel assets, controlling inventory costs, and supporting accurate financial reporting.</p><h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><p><strong>Receiving</strong></p><ul><li><p>Receive, inspect, and verify all incoming goods against purchase orders and delivery notes</p></li><li><p>Ensure quantities, quality, specifications, and prices are correct before acceptance</p></li><li><p>Reject or report damaged, incorrect, or substandard goods to the relevant department</p></li><li><p>Ensure all received items are properly documented and signed</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with suppliers, Purchasing, and operating departments on delivery issues</p></li></ul><p><strong>Cost Control</strong></p><ul><li><p>Verify supplier invoices against purchase orders and receiving records</p></li><li><p>Monitor daily food, beverage, and operating supplies costs</p></li><li><p>Assist in maintaining accurate inventory and stock movement records</p></li><li><p>Support month-end stock take and inventory counts</p></li><li><p>Highlight cost variances, discrepancies, or unusual usage to the Cost Controller / Finance Manager</p></li></ul><p><strong>Compliance & Documentation</strong></p><ul><li><p>Maintain proper filing of receiving documents, invoices, and cost reports</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with hotel policies, internal controls, and audit requirements</p></li><li><p>Follow hygiene, safety, and security procedures at the receiving bay</p></li></ul><p><strong>General</strong></p><ul><li><p>Work closely with F&B, Kitchen, Engineering, and Housekeeping teams</p></li><li><p>Perform ad-hoc finance or store-related duties as assigned</p></li></ul>",
